First Lady Melania Trump and President Donald J. Trump are hosting the annual Easter Egg Roll at the White House. This year, attendees can participate in activities such as the Egg Roll, the Cards for Troops station, musical eggs, and Be Best hopscotch. In addition, children will have the opportunity to spread kindness by mailing postcards to anyone they choose through a United States Postal Service mailbox on the South grounds. The event is expected to have over 30,000 attendees and will include various entertainment and reading nook readers.